We believe we've identified the cause behind some miners' incentives unexpectedly dropping to zero. It appears that the issue is related to several factors on the Validator's end, and also Miner's side:

- some validators are not running the latest version of the AudioSubnet code. Some are even operating on version 2.1.3, as identified by the following hotkeys: 5CaNj3BarTHotEK1n513aoTtFeXcjf6uvKzAyzNuv9cirUoW; 5EhvL1FVkQPpMjZX4MAADcW42i3xPSF1KiCpuaxTYVr28sux
- some validators are missing the MISQA scoring file from the AudioSubnet repo and is actually scoring each TTS and VC output with 0 score, notably observed with the hotkey: 5EhvL1FVkQPpMjZX4MAADcW42i3xPSF1KiCpuaxTYVr28sux
- some validators machines lack sufficient resources (VRAM) and are struggling to score miners accurately. With the recent introduction of the Text-to-Music service, validators now require a minimum of 48 GB of VRAM for the CLAP metric to function correctly.
- some miners are still using 4090 (and that's not enough) or A6000 GPUs, but the DL performance is not that good (this applies to runpod/vastai machines). Also, having fast internet and enough RAM is very important.
